{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Queensland | title = 2018 Ipswich SuperSprint | round_no = 9 | season_no = 16 | year = 2018 | series = SC | track_map = Queensland Raceway (Australia) track map -- National Circuit.svg | date = 20–22 July | location = [[Willowbank, Queensland|Willowbank]], [[Queensland]] | circuit = Queensland Raceway | weather = | race1_laps = 39 | race1_dist = 121.763 | pole1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole1_time = 1:08.5014 | winner1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | winner1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | winner1_time = 46:40.8180 | race2_laps = 65 | race2_dist = 202.938 | pole2 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole2_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole2_time = 1:08.4899 | winner2 = {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Shane van Gisbergen]]}} | winner2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | winner2_time = 1:18:33.4917 }} The '''2018 Ipswich SuperSprint''' (formally known as '''2018 Coates Hire Ipswich SuperSprint''') was an [[auto racing|motor racing]] event for the [[Supercars Championship]], held on the weekend of 20–22 July 2018. The event was held at [[Queensland Raceway]] near [[Ipswich, Queensland]] and consisted of two races, 120 and 200 kilometres in length. It was the ninth event of sixteen in the [[2018 Supercars Championship]] and hosted Races 19 and 20 of the season.
