{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Queensland | title = 2018 Townsville 400 | round_no = 8 | season_no = 16 | year = 2018 | series = SC | track_map = Townsville (Australia) street circuit track map.svg | date = 6-8 July | location = [[Townsville]], [[Queensland]] | circuit = Townsville Street Circuit | weather = | race1_laps = 70 | race1_dist = 200.524 | pole1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole1_time = 1:12.1239 | winner1 = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Jamie Whincup]] | winner1_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | winner1_time = 1:30:53.1102 | race2_laps = 70 | race2_dist = 200.524 | pole2 = {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Shane van Gisbergen]]}} | pole2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | pole2_time = 1:12.1042 | winner2 = {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Shane van Gisbergen]]}} | winner2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | winner2_time = 1:31:05.6781 }} The '''2018 Townsville 400''' (formally known as '''2018 Watpac Townsville 400''') was a [[auto racing|motor racing]] event for the [[Supercars Championship]], held on the weekend of 6-8 July 2018. The event was held at [[Townsville Street Circuit]] near [[Townsville]], [[Queensland]] and consisted of two races, both 200 kilometres in length. It was the eighth event of sixteen in the [[2018 Supercars Championship]] and hosted Races 17 and 18 of the season.
