[[File:Lacrosse catch1.jpg|thumb|250px|A [[lacrosse]] player wearing a scrimmage vest, the dark blue garment]]

A '''scrimmage vest''', sometimes referred to as a '''[[Pinafore|pinnie]]''', is a piece of [[clothing]] or [[clothing|sportswear]], often made of mesh, used in practices as a substitute for a sports team's usual uniform or to differentiate temporary teams in informal scrimmages. Some teams elect to have benched players wear them during a game. A vest can come in a variety of forms, including a racerback cut,<ref>https://www.lacrossepinnies.com/blog/pinnys/</ref> collegiate cut, [[basketball]] cut or [[lacrosse]] pinnie.

Vests are usually made from poly-mesh material. [[Screen printing]] or vinyl heat press artwork is often applied directly to the mesh. New techniques include [[Dye-sublimation printer|dye-sublimation]].

